Responsibilities:

  Establish high level design on the IAM processes, solution architecture, and integration requirements;
  Conduct a workshop with client’s stakeholders to gather business and functional requirements;
  Document business and functional requirements into Functional Specification document;
  Review Test Plan and Test Cases prepared by QA team according to use cases defined in the Functional Specification document;
  Participate  in System Integration Test (SIT) and User Acceptance Test (UAT) and  coordinate with DI QA team, application developers and client to clarify  any issues arising during SIT and UAT.
  Conduct functional level solution training;
  Develop the required documentations (e.g. Administrator Guide, User Guide, Operation Guide, etc);
  Assist during Go-Live activities; and during Warranty or Support period.


Requirements:

  Possessing Bachelor's degree or technical equivalent
  At least 6 years of working experience in Identity &amp; Access Management (IAM) field
  Confident to lead the discussion with various project stakeholders
  Strong communication skill


